  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Risk Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A potential event or future situation that can potentially affect, prevent, or limit a project's success.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;Examples of potential sources of risk in software development are listed below:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Requirements&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Design&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Development process&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Work environment&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Resources&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Risk Attributes&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;b>Risk Description:&lt;/b> A description of the risk detailing the impact for the project if this risk becomes a&#xD;
        problem&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;b>Risk Category&lt;/b>: Such as technical, project management, organizational, and external.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;b>Risk Type:&lt;/b> Such as Direct or Indirect, resource risk (time, people), technical risk(scope, technology or&#xD;
        external deendency)&amp;nbsp;or schedule risk.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Risk Severity:&lt;/strong> The extent of the impact if the problem occurs.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Risk Magnitude:&lt;/strong> Scale use to prioritize the risk.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Risk Responses:&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;b>Avoid&lt;/b>: Reorganize the project so that it cannot be affected by that risk. For example removing&amp;nbsp;work or&#xD;
        avoiding the use of&amp;nbsp;certain techonlogies &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;b>Mitigate&lt;/b>: Define actions to reduce the probability or the impact of the risk. For example, addressing high&#xD;
        risk concern first.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;b>Transfer&lt;/b>: Reorganize the project so that someone or something else bears the risk. Is not recommended for&#xD;
        college work as the students are responsable for the their work.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
